author: NEW YORK DAILY NEWS
title: SEE IT: Drivers in China suffer through insane traffic jam
text:
Sploid/YouTube A traffic jam is seen in Beijing, China. Sploid/YouTube There were a reported 750 million people in traffic. Sploid/YouTube A video by a drone captures a traffic jam in Beijing, China, following a national holiday week. Previous Next Enlarge The next time the urge to complain about slow traffic sets in, just have a glance at this epic back-up in Beijing, China, near the border of Hong Kong.
About 750 million commuters, or half of China's population, were forced to sit in traffic on the G4 Beijing - Hong Kong - Macau Expressway on Oct. 6, People's Daily, China reported.
A video taken overhead by drone - the only mode of cutting quickly through the jam - captured the slow scooting traffic, caused largely in part to a security checkpoint.
